				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$I_{r} ,$$\end{document} was calculated by multiplying the squared radial distances (d) of each outer pixel (i) to the boundary with the area of each pixel (i.e., the pixel size) (dA) and summing over all the outer pixels, Eq. (4).4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
